Bambusa polymorpha

   [3624.jpg]
    Authority   Munro.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3624

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A large, handsome tufted bamboo with tall, clean culms reaching 25-30 m
   in height and 15 cm in diameter. Evergreen or deciduous under drier
   conditions.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial. The life-cycle is about 60 years.
   COMMON NAMES
   Kyathaungwa.
   FURTHER INF
   Kyathaungwa is usually found on lower slopes or in well drained
   valleys, often indicating deep, fertile and well drained soils. Bamboos
   grow between the latitudes 40°N and S. Though the big bamboo forests
   usually occur between 15-25°N and S.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Hassan M 1988 pp 505-513 [RAIN, TEMP, SAL, DRA, TEXT, PH, DEP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 417 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 8 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Troup R 1921 pp 978 1002-1003 [DRA, FER, DEP, TEXT, USE]

